eu.opends.analyzer

Class DataUnit

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.opends.analyzer.DataUnit
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class DataUnit
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Data object containing position and speed of the car, as well as the current date. Based on AnalyzationData.java from the CARS-project.
    Author:
    Marco Mueller, Rafael Math
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

        The default constructor used in simulator.
        Parameters:
        xpos - The position of the car on the x axis.
        ypos - The position of the car on the y axis.
        zpos - The position of the car on the z axis.
        speed - The current speed of the car in kilometers per hour.
        date - The date, when the data set was taken.
        steeringWheelPos - The position of the steering wheel: -1 full left, 0 centered, 1 full right.
        gasPedalPos - The position of the gas pedal: 0 no acceleration, 1 full acceleration
        brakePedalPos - The position of the brake pedal: -1 full break/negative acceleration, 0 no acceleration
